%N A394188 Number of partitions of n such that (number of distinct parts) <= minimal multiplicity of the parts.
%H A394188 Seiichi Manyama, <a href="/A394188/b394188.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000</a>
%F A394188 G.f.: Sum_{j>=0} [z^j] Product_{k>=1} (1 + z*q^(j*k)/(1-q^k)).
%e A394188 a(8) = 7 counts these partitions: 8, 44, 3311, 2222, 22211, 221111, 11111111.
%o A394188 (PARI) my(N=70, q='q+O('q^N)); Vec(sum(j=0, N, polcoef(prod(k=1, N, 1+z*q^(j*k)/(1-q^k)), j, z)))
